Title: Synthesis
Body: MIME-Version: 1.0 Server: CERN/3.0 Date: Monday, 25-Nov-96 00:31:53 GMT Content-Type: text/html Content-Length: 1546 Last-Modified: Tuesday, 24-Oct-95 14:18:31 GMT Synthesis Research Summary Three bottlenecks exist in scientific computing, generating the effective software for complicated mathematical problems, running the software on a machine, and interpreting, or visualizing, the large body of data that is produced by the computation.
